Sri Lanka Telecom Advances on Quarterly Profit, Dividend

-- B y   A n u s h a   O n d a a t j i e
-- 
2011-02-24T04:33:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/sri-lanka-telecom-advances-on-quarterly-profit-dividend.html
  Sri Lanka Telecom Plc  rose as much
as 4.2 percent in Colombo trading after reporting a fourth-
quarter profit. The shares changed hands at 61.90 rupees at 9:55
a.m. local time.  Net income was 1.54 billion rupees ($13.9 million) in the
three months ended Dec. 31, compared with a loss of 379 million
rupees a year earlier, according to a filing to the  Colombo
Stock Exchange . Sri Lanka Telecom said it will pay a dividend of
60 Sri Lankan cents a share.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anusha Ondaatjie in Colombo at 
 anushao@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Hari Govind at 
 hgovind@bloomberg.net  